name: The Network
description: Moll may have given the crew of the Discovery the slip, but bigger problems loom on the horizon. When the Discovery crew's past returns to haunt them, can you sift out the truth and set things right?
rules:
-- Unique Supply Missions are available during the event. Open the Event to access them.
-- Using Moll, any version of Hy'Rell, Culber, Detmer, or Discovery crew will provide a bonus to Supply Missions.
-- Every Supply Mission you complete earns you Event Victory Points. Collect Event Victory Points to unlock Threshold Rewards!
-- Community Rewards are only available during Phase 1. Collect Event Victory Points to unlock these rewards before the phase change!
-- In this event, Squadrons may also compete to advance up the Squadron leaderboards. Join a Squadron to get more rewards!
bonus_text: Crew Bonus: Moll, Hy'Rell, Culber, Detmer, or Discovery crew
rewards_teaser: Reach Rank 1 by gaining Victory Points from Event Supply Missions!

screens.text: "Thank you for responding to our distress hails, Captain. Captain Burnham said you would be the most appropriate one to field our concerns, as she was on a pursuit of great importance."

"Artifacts related to the Federation vessel U.S.S. Discovery, under registry numbers NCC-1031 and NCC-1031-A, have been stolen from the Eternal Gallery and Archive. We are unable go identify whom, how, or what for, but we are hopeful you can assist us in that matter."
"Well, that's interesting. This can't be a coincidence with Moll initiating another race across the stars. But why steal artifacts from Discovery's past?"
"Your guess is as good as mine. But if Moll really was behind this, we need to get those artifacts back. I doubt any good would come from her having them."
